WEDNESDAY, AUGUST 3   

8:45 - 1:00   Networking Testbeds Field Trip          
Visits to the testbeds will last about one hour.  Visits will be 
staggered to accommodate as many attendees as possible.

FIELD TRIP DESCRIPTION: 
On the morning of August 3, we will coordinate visits to two local
high-speed networking testbed sites.  At the Lawrence Berkeley
Laboratory, researchers will demonstrate the MAGIC testbed's Image
Server System technology (as presented in the paper by Tierney et al.),
as well as a teleconferencing application that runs over OC-3 (155
Mbps) links on the Bay Area Gigabit Network (BAGNet).  At the
University of California, Berkeley, researchers will demonstrate
teleconferncing and scientific visualization applications running over
XUNET (45 Mbps) and BLANCA (622 Mbps).  Visitors will also have the
opportunity to see as much of the supporting hardware as possible.

Complementary shuttle is provided for High-Speed Testbed visits.

BIRDS OF A FEATHER SESSIONS:  On Monday evening, August 1, space
is available for Birds of a Feather Sessions.  You can schedule your
BOF upon your arrival to the Symposium with a USENIX Staff
person.

